# Postgres + pgvector (HNSW) for `<project-name>`

This directory holds the database init for `<project-name>`'s RAG store. It
**reuses** the B.8.5 `pgvector/pgvector:0.8.2-pg17` image (no new infra
component — `NFR-B7-2-001`) and adds only the RAG-specific schema + indexes.

## Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `init-pgvector.sql` | Runs once on first DB init (`docker-entrypoint-initdb.d`). Enables the `vector` extension, creates the `rag_chunks` table, and builds the HNSW (`vector_cosine_ops`) + full-text (GIN) indexes that hybrid retrieval depends on. |

## HNSW index

The RAG pipeline's dense-vector retrieval leg queries the `rag_chunks_embedding_hnsw`
index (`USING hnsw (embedding vector_cosine_ops)`). The sparse BM25 leg uses the
`rag_chunks_content_fts` GIN index; the two are fused via Reciprocal Rank Fusion
(RRF) in `backend/rag/`. See `.forge/standards/global/rag-patterns.md`.

The `vector(384)` dimension matches the default `LocalEmbedder` model
(AllMiniLML6V2). Change it to match your embeddings provider before loading data.
